// Journal strings

//Quest start
@12000 = ~The Perfect Poison

In the Slums of Athkatla, an Eldathyn named Merethan approached me about an incurable toxin spreading through the lands. He believes a shadowy poison supplier is behind it and asked for my help to trace the source.~

@12001 = ~The Perfect Poison

Merethan pointed me to Skann Delth, a small-time poison peddler who loiters on the Copper Coronet’s rooftop. I’m to press him for the origin of his deadliest wares. Merethan is waiting for me at the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums of Athkatla.~

@12002 = ~The Perfect Poison

I confronted Skann Delth and obtained a map to a secluded site called Toadstool Hollow. I must bring this map to Merethan, who awaits me at the Temple of Ilmater in the slums of Athkatla.~

@12003 = ~The Perfect Poison

Merethan wishes me to accompany him to Toadstool Hollow to see whether the poisoner will reveal himself. He awaits me at the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums so that we may depart together.~

@12004 = ~The Perfect Poison

At Toadstool Hollow, a supposed exchange turned into an ambush. The mysterious poisoner’s servant struck down Merethan, yet one of the arrows remained laced with the toxin. Before passing, he entrusted the arrow to me and urged that it be taken to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell, Eldath's sanctuary.~

@12005 = ~The Perfect Poison

Fallskeeper Alatoasz believes that the key to understanding the poison lies within the ruins of an ancient elven city. He suspects the rare plant used to create it may grow there. To narrow our search, he has asked me to visit the Temple of Oghma in Athkatla and consult their tomes on the lost kingdom of Keltormir.~

@12006 = ~The Perfect Poison

I returned the tome from the Temple of Oghma to Fallskeeper Alatoasz. Its passages point to Myth Unnohyr: a ruined elven city whose shattered mythal breeds wild magic by day and dead magic by night. The taint has seeped into a rare plant used to craft the incurable poison. He marked the ruins on my map. I must travel to Myth Unnohyr, find the poisoner—a Malagent of Talona—and bring back a blossom of the corrupted plant so the Fallskeeper can attempt an antidote.~

@12007 = ~The Perfect Poison

I confronted the Malagent deep within the ruins of Myth Unnohyr. He confessed to fusing corrupt mythal magic into a novel toxin and boasted that multiple batches had already been distributed across Amn. He vowed to turn Myth Unnohyr into his lady’s toxic domain—but I put an end to his schemes. I must now bring a sample of the corrupted plant back to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell so that an antidote can be created.~

@12008 = ~The Perfect Poison

I have found the corrupted plant known as Groveglove—the source of the perfect poison. After defeating the Malagent, I must bring this sample to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell, so he can attempt to cleanse its essence and brew an antidote.~

@12009 = ~The Perfect Poison

The Malagent is dead, and his vile work lies in ruins. I brought the Groveglove plant to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell, who believes an antidote can be created to counter the poison already spread across Amn. Yet to purify the tainted flower and craft the cure, further aid from other faiths will be required.~

// The antidote

@12100 = ~The Antidote

Fallskeeper Alatoasz believes the Groveglove flower can be cleansed and turned into an antidote. To succeed, the flower must be blessed three times—with the divine aspects of Life, Compassion, and Renewal. Alatoasz has granted me the first blessing himself, but I must seek out the other two.~

@12101 = ~The Antidote: Ilmater's Blessing of Compassion

I am to travel to the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums of Athkatla and request the Blessing of Compassion. The Fallskeeper believes the Ilmateri will aid our cause without hesitation.~

@12102 = ~The Antidote: Lathander's Blessing of Renewal

I must visit the Church of Lathander in Athkatla to receive the Blessing of Renewal.~

@12103 = ~The Antidote: Eldath’s singing water

Alatoasz has instructed me to collect a carafe of Eldath’s singing water from the grotto in Duskwood Dell. One of the handmaidens tending the sacred pool will provide it. The water will serve as the final medium through which the blessings must be combined.~

@12104 = ~The Antidote: Ilmater's Blessing of Compassion

I have received the Blessing of Compassion from the Ilmateri in the Slums. Their prayer imbued the Groveglove with a faint warmth—as if the flower itself responded to mercy.~

@12105 = ~The Antidote: Lathander's Blessing of Renewal

The priests of Lathander have bestowed the Blessing of Renewal. Bathed in sunlight, the Groveglove seemed to stir, its dark hue paling ever so slightly under the Morninglord’s grace.~

@12106 = ~The Antidote: Eldath’s singing water

I have obtained a jug of Eldath’s singing water from the grotto in Duskwood Dell. Its surface hums softly, reflecting every breath of the forest. Now all that remains is to return to Fallskeeper Alatoasz with the blessed flower and the sacred water.~

@12107 = ~The Antidote

All three blessings have been gathered—Life, Compassion, and Renewal—and I have secured Eldath’s singing water. I must now return to Fallskeeper Alatoasz in Duskwood Dell so that the antidote can finally be created and the corruption of the Groveglove purged once and for all.~

@12108 = ~The Antidote

I have gathered all that was required: the Groveglove flower, the blessings, and a carafe of Eldath’s singing water. Fallskeeper Alatoasz believes that to forge the antidote, the sanctified flower and the sacred water must be placed within the Malagent’s cauldron in the ruins of Myth Unnohyr—the very place where the poison was first brewed.~

@12110 = ~The Antidote

The ritual succeeded. From the Malagent’s corrupted cauldron rose a monstrous Poison Incarnation—an embodiment of the toxin’s final wrath. I destroyed it, and the Groveglove’s corruption was purged. The antidote has taken shape, shimmering with a calm, emerald light. I must bring it back to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell.~

@12111 = ~The Antidote

I delivered the antidote to Alatoasz Berendim, and he accepted it with gratitude. The venom that once threatened the Lands of Intrigue can spread no further.~

/******************************
SIDE quest journal entries
******************************/
// Duskwood Dell – Missing Faerie Twins Quest

@13000 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

The faeries of Duskwood Dell are missing. Brother Edrim has asked me to look into their disappearance. The twins were last seen speaking with a merchant dressed in bright red silk, who spoke with a strange accent — a rolling "r". He continued west toward Athkatla and may be hiding among the traders of Waukeen’s Promenade. If he truly traffics in magical curiosities, I’ll find him there.~

@13001 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

Among the stalls of Waukeen’s Promenade, I have encountered a curious merchant who fits Brother Edrim’s description — a man in red silk, dealing in peculiar items and speaking with a strange, almost hypnotic charm. Something about him feels... wrong.~

@13002 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

The merchant calling himself Zar’khaan was no merchant at all, but a Rakshasa in disguise. I must find out if he carries the Dell-Light Twins with him — perhaps sealed within some kind of small vessel or enchanted trinket.~

@13003 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

I have found the Dell-Light Twins. The Rakshasa imprisoned them within a magical vessel sealed by powerful enchantment. Though the faeries seem unharmed, the jar refuses to open. I should return it to Brother Edrim in Duskwood Dell — perhaps he will know how to break the seal.~

@13004 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

I have brought the faerie glass back to Brother Edrim in Duskwood Dell. He was able to break the seal, and the Dell-Light Twins have emerged unharmed. Their laughter once again dances through Duskwood Dell. Peace — and some mischief — have returned to this quiet corner of the world.~

// Mythal forge amulet
@13010 = ~Binding the Unbound

Among the remains of a dead mage I found a letter describing the shattered Mythal of Myth Unnohyr. He believed it might be possible to forge an ancient elven talisman able to resist the Mythal’s corruption—if one could combine the essences of two rare wisps, born of wild and dead magic, with the relic itself.~

@13011 = ~Binding the Unbound

I discovered an ancient elven anvil, its surface still smooth despite the passing of centuries. It was once used to craft fine ornaments and sacred relics. If any place could bind magic anew, it would be here.~

@13012 = ~Binding the Unbound

I have found a delicate elven chain—likely part of a talisman. It must once have carried a pendant of some kind.~

@13013 = ~Binding the Unbound

I discovered a finely wrought amulet head, clearly elven in design. Its socket seems made to hold a chain. If restored, the two could form a complete talisman.~

@13014 = ~Binding the Unbound

I obtained the essence of a Will-o’-Wild, a luminous fragment of chaotic energy that seems to hum with the pulse of living magic.~

@13015 = ~Binding the Unbound

I have captured the essence of a Will-o’-Dead. Its shadowed glow feels cold to the touch, filled with the silence of dead magic.~

@13016 = ~Binding the Unbound

I now possess all that is needed to forge the talisman described in the mage’s letter: the elven chain, the amulet head, and the twin essences of the wisps—one of wild magic, one of dead. Perhaps at the ancient anvil I found, their powers can be joined.~

@13017 = ~Binding the Unbound

At the old anvil I combined the two wisp essences with the restored elven talisman. The relic has awakened—its glow faint but steady. The Mythal’s corruption no longer affects the spells of the talisman’s wearer.~

// Banshee seeking head:
@13020 = ~Lament of the Lost

In the upper reaches of a ruined tower in Myth Unnohyr I encountered the spirit of a banshee, forever lamenting the death of her beloved. She seeks something to remember him by—something that might finally let her spirit rest.~

@13021 = ~Lament of the Lost

I found a severed elven head within the ruins of Myth Unnohyr—its features strangely peaceful despite its grim fate.~

@13022 = ~Lament of the Lost

I returned the head of her beloved to the banshee. She whispered a final sigh and vanished, her sorrow finally laid to rest.~

@13023 = ~Lament of the Lost

I destroyed a banshee haunting a ruined tower in Myth Unnohyr. Her wail has fallen silent, and her grief will trouble this place no more.~

// Honeymead Quest
@13030 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

In Duskwood Dell I met an Eldathyn beekeeper who produces a rare honeymead. He asked me to take a single bottle to the Five Flagons Inn in Athkatla and sell it to Samuel Thunderburp for a fair price.~

@13032 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I sold the bottle of Honeymead to Samuel Thunderburp for one hundred gold pieces. He seemed content enough with the deal.~

@13033 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I sold the bottle of Honeymead to Samuel Thunderburp for five hundred gold pieces. A fair exchange for such a refined brew.~

@13034 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I sold the bottle of Honeymead to Samuel Thunderburp for seven hundred and fifty gold pieces. The innkeeper praised its quality and generosity flowed as freely as his coin.~

@13035 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I sold the bottle of Honeymead to Samuel Thunderburp for one thousand gold pieces. He called it a nectar beyond price—and paid accordingly.~

@13036 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I returned to the beekeeper in Duskwood Dell and brought him one hundred gold pieces for the honeymead. He accepted the payment with quiet disappointment.~

@13037 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I returned to the beekeeper in Duskwood Dell and delivered five hundred gold pieces for the honeymead. He smiled faintly, grateful for my honesty.~

@13038 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I brought the beekeeper seven hundred and fifty gold pieces for the honeymead. He was pleasantly surprised, murmuring that Eldath’s blessings come in many forms.~

@13039 = ~The Eldathyn Honeymead

I returned to the beekeeper with one thousand gold pieces for the honeymead. He was astonished by my generosity and offered a heartfelt prayer in my name.~

// Boy and worm

@13040 = ~The Little Angler

A boy by the pier in Duskwood Dell asked me to help him find a worm for fishing. He said he wants to prove to everyone that he can catch a real fish all by himself.~

@13041 = ~The Little Angler

I found a worm wriggling in the soft soil of Duskwood Dell. Perhaps this is the lucky catch the boy was looking for.~

@13042 = ~The Little Angler

I gave the worm to the boy by the pier. Instead of using it as bait, he decided to keep it as a pet and named it Noodle. The two seem rather happy together.~

@13043 = ~The Little Angler

I threw the worm into the water instead of giving it to the boy. He burst into tears, called me horrible names, and ran off. I doubt I’ll be welcome by the pier again.~

// Montrassa - emblem
@13050 = ~The Emblem of Eldath

In Duskwood Dell I met an elderly Eldathyn named Montrassa. Her hands tremble with age, and she can no longer carve the holy emblems she once made for her temple. She spoke fondly of Merethan but humbly refused to take his emblem, saying that such a gift should be granted only with the blessing of the High Fallskeeper. Perhaps I should speak with Alatoasz Berendim about it.~

@13051 = ~The Emblem of Eldath

Alatoasz agreed that Montrassa is worthy to carry Merethan’s emblem. I should deliver it to her in Duskwood Dell so she may hold the symbol of her goddess once more.~

@13052 = ~The Emblem of Eldath

I gave Merethan’s emblem to Montrassa. Her gratitude was quiet yet profound—she said she would carry my name in her prayers to the Lady of Still Waters.~

// Siren
@13060 = ~The Siren’s Fury

In Duskwood Dell I met a siren tormented by anger and grief. She came seeking peace in Eldath’s grove, yet fury still clings to her like salt upon the tide. Perhaps someone in the Dell knows how to soothe her unrest.~

@13061 = ~The Siren’s Fury

An elderly Eldathyn priestess entrusted me with a mug of herbal brew. She believes it may calm the siren’s heart if given beneath the open sky.~

@13062 = ~The Siren’s Fury

I gave the blessed brew to the siren. In gratitude she offered me her old arrows, saying they had carried her rage for too long.~


//HALFLING
@13072 = ~The halfling merchant

I met a halfling merchant named Debbie Gobblebubble in the wilderness. She decided to travel to Trademeet, where her cooking and wares might find a warmer welcome.~

@13073 = ~The halfling merchant

I met a halfling merchant named Debbie Gobblebubble in the wilderness. She has set out for Athkatla to try her luck among the merchants and wanderers of Waukeen’s Promenade.~

@13074 = ~The halfling merchant

I met a halfling merchant named Debbie Gobblebubble in the wilderness. She chose to head for the Abbey of the Goldspires, the sacred haven of merchants devoted to Waukeen.~

// Mannatarv wants to die
@13080 = ~A Peaceful Death

In Duskwood Dell I met an old man named Mannatarv. He is frail and weary of life, yet the priests of Eldath refuse to let him die. He asked me to bring him a leaf of the Groveglove before an antidote is made, so that he might finally leave this world in silence.~

@13081 = ~A Peaceful Death

I agreed to Mannatarv’s request. He waits in the infirmary of Duskwood Dell for the poisonous leaf, ready to end his suffering when I return.~

@13082 = ~A Peaceful Death

I gave Mannatarv a leaf of the Groveglove. He thanked me for granting the mercy others would not—and passed away peacefully soon after.~

@13083 = ~A Peaceful Death

I refused to help Mannatarv end his life. The priests of Eldath will keep him alive through their healing, whether he wishes it or not. I can only hope he finds peace in their care—or in his dreams.~

// Wadal Hrun
@13090 = ~The Poisoner’s Tower

I encountered one of the Talonite’s yuan-ti servants near the poisoned ruins of Myth Unnohyr. The creature has gone into hiding somewhere within the city, and the entrance to the poisoner’s tower remains sealed by some unknown ward.~

@13091 = ~The Poisoner’s Tower

I killed the yuan-ti servant. Among its belongings was a small ioun stone, smooth and berry-shaped, humming faintly with trapped venomous light. It likely serves as the key to the poisoner’s tower.~

// Grotto quest
@13110 = ~Where Steel Grows Silent

The maiden of the grotto in Duskwood Dell offered to take any weapons I no longer need, to lay them to rest in Eldath’s sacred pool. She promised that by doing so, I would please the Quiet One and receive her blessing—along with a touch of renewed vitality.~

@13111 = ~Where Steel Grows Silent

I offered one of my weapons to the pool, as the maiden asked. The water shimmered faintly as the steel sank beneath the surface, swallowed by calm. In that quiet, I felt a fleeting touch of Eldath’s peace—gentle, wordless, and whole.~

// Runaway Nephew
@13120 = ~The Runaway Nephew

In Duskwood Dell I met a young man who fled from his aunt in Athkatla’s Government District. Raised among marble and coin, he yearned for a simpler life and found peace among Eldath’s faithful. He asked me to bring his aunt a flower and tell her that he is safe.~

@13121 = ~The Runaway Nephew

I met the boy’s aunt in the Government District of Athkatla. At first she was furious, but the message—and the flower—softened her anger. She said that next time, he should bring the flowers himself.~

@13122 = ~The Runaway Nephew

I returned to the boy in Duskwood Dell and told him of his aunt’s words. At last, he can focus on the life he truly wanted to live.~

@13123 = ~The Runaway Nephew

I met the boy’s aunt in the Government District of Athkatla and delivered the flower.~


// Coinquest
@13130 = ~The Promise Unkept

I found a crumpled note on a dead adventurer. It spoke of a nightly meeting behind the Temple of Helm in Athkatla's Bridge District to get what someone has been asking for. The note was addressed to a man named Marrik. I also found a worn coin showing the face of an elderly man. Perhaps the two are connected.~

@13131 = ~The Promise Unkept

Behind the Temple of Helm in the Bridge District, I met a man and showed him the token. He sent me to another meeting place behind the Temple of Lathander in the Temple District — again, after dark. He said I’d get what I came for, though I’ve no idea what that’s supposed to mean.~

@13132 = ~The Promise Unkept

Behind the Temple of Lathander, my presence — and the coin — seemed expected. The man there claimed the next gathering would be at the Temple of Waukeen in the Government District, when night falls. No one has yet explained what I am meant to receive.~

@13133 = ~The Promise Unkept

Atthe Temple of Waukeen, I was sent once more on. They spoke of a final meeting, this time at night behind the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums. Each promise sounds the same: that I will get what I wanted. Yet I am no longer sure what that is.~

@13134 = ~The Promise Unkept

Behind the Temple of Ilmater I finally met the man all the others had spoken of. He asked about a geas I was supposed to be bound by — yet the letter I carried belonged to someone long dead. Whatever burden or plea the original sender hoped to resolve ended elsewhere, and none of it had anything to do with me.~







































